A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL OFFENSES -- PUBLIC UTILITIES
Introduced By: Representatives Fogarty, Carson, Cotter, Noret, Hull, Tanzi, Bennett,
Dawson, Cortvriend, and Shallcross Smith
Date Introduced: February 12, 2025
Referred To: House Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 11-35-18 of the General Laws in Chapter 11-35 entitled "Public
2 Utilities" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 11-35-18. Bomb threats and similar false reports.
4 (a) Whoever, knowing the report to be false, transmits or causes to be transmitted to any
5 person by telephone or other means a communication falsely reporting, warning, or threatening
6 either the location existence of any explosive or other dangerous substance or contrivance, or a
7 shooting or other dangerous event or happening, at a location, causing terror, anxiety, unrest, fear,
8 or personal discomfort by that false report, warning, or threat to any person or group of persons, or
9 prompting an evacuation or lockdown of a location or other law enforcement response, shall be
10 guilty of a felony and shall be punished by imprisonment at the adult correctional institutions for
11 not more than ten (10) years, or by a fine of not more than one thousand dollars ($1,000), or by
12 both fine and imprisonment.
13 (b) For any person charged under subsection (a) of this section, the court may consider any
14 factors, including whether the person poses a danger to any individual, the community, or the
15 defendant, when making bail determinations, and may impose any reasonable conditions or court
16 order, including, but not limited to:
17 (1) An extreme risk protection order pursuant to the provisions of chapter 8.3 of title 8;
18 (2) A no trespass order for any educational, religious, or public institution or building;
19 (3) A mental health assessment and/or a referral for mental health treatment; and/or

1 (4) Substance abuse counseling.
2 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
